ities on top of the `libc` crate:\n> \n> * `errno`\n> * `fork`\n> * `poll`\n> * `signal`\n> * `ioctl`\n> * `timerfd`\n> * `eventfd`\n> * `syslog`\n> * `terminal`\n> \n> ## Why is this crate relevant to the rust-vmm project?\n> \n> Although this crate could be used by many projects not related to VMMs or virtualization at all, this set of tools and helpers make writing a VMM easier and shorter than using the `libc` crate directly.\n\nDoesn't the nix crate have this stuff already?\n\nIMHO if it's general stuff then we should contribute to the\nlibc/nix/whatever crates as needed rather than spinning our own.\n\nDave\n\n> \n> -- \n> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28\n--\nDr. David Alan Gilbert / dgilbert@redhat.com / Manchester, UK\n", "updated_at": "2019-02-26T14:25:56Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/467457968", "author_association": "NONE", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-467457968", "created_at": "2019-02-26T14:25:56Z", "id": 467457968, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2NzQ1Nzk2OA=="}, {"user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/following{/other_user}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo", "site_admin": false, "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/gists{/gist_id}", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDM4NjM=", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "gravatar_id": "", "id": 1043863, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/events{/privacy}", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1043863?v=4", "login": "sameo", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/repos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/subscriptions", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/followers", "html_url": "https://github.com/sameo", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/received_events", "type": "User", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/orgs"}, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/28", "body": "> > * Samuel Ortiz (notifications@github.com) wrote:\r\n> > Although this crate could be used by many projects not related to VMMs or virtualization at all, this set of tools and helpers make writing a VMM easier and shorter than using the `libc` crate directly.\r\n\r\n> Doesn't the nix crate have this stuff already? IMHO if it's general stuff then we should contribute to the libc/nix/whatever crates as needed rather than spinning our own. \r\n\r\nAfter looking at `nix`, I think in some cases it does have roughly what we need, in other cases it does not. Overall, I find this crate to be very large and in some cases complex for what we're trying to achieve. We need a small subset of `nix` and I feel this is a case where we may prefer to have our own smaller implementation than add one more, fairly large dependency.", "updated_at": "2019-02-27T23:42:45Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/468076013", "author_association": "MEMBER", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-468076013", "created_at": "2019-02-27T23:42:45Z", "id": 468076013, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2ODA3NjAxMw=="}, {"user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/following{/other_user}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2", "site_admin": false, "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/gists{/gist_id}", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM5Njg0NjQ5", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "gravatar_id": "", "id": 39684649, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/events{/privacy}", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/39684649?v=4", "login": "liujing2", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/repos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/subscriptions", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/followers", "html_url": "https://github.com/liujing2", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/received_events", "type": "User", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/liujing2/orgs"}, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/28", "body": "@sameo fork might only be created by crosvm now, and I found all the functions in fork.rs are not used, expect the #[test] inside. Do we still need fork crate?", "updated_at": "2019-02-28T13:08:22Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/468266127", "author_association": "MEMBER", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-468266127", "created_at": "2019-02-28T13:08:22Z", "id": 468266127, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2ODI2NjEyNw=="}, {"user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/following{/other_user}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo", "site_admin": false, "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/gists{/gist_id}", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDM4NjM=", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "gravatar_id": "", "id": 1043863, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/events{/privacy}", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1043863?v=4", "login": "sameo", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/repos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/subscriptions", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/followers", "html_url": "https://github.com/sameo", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/received_events", "type": "User", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/orgs"}, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/28", "body": "@liujing2 If neither crosvm nor FC use it, then we should not add it for now.", "updated_at": "2019-03-03T19:13:31Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/469053858", "author_association": "MEMBER", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-469053858", "created_at": "2019-03-03T19:13:31Z", "id": 469053858, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ2OTA1Mzg1OA=="}, {"user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/following{/other_user}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo", "site_admin": false, "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/gists{/gist_id}", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDM4NjM=", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "gravatar_id": "", "id": 1043863, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/events{/privacy}", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1043863?v=4", "login": "sameo", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/repos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/subscriptions", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/followers", "html_url": "https://github.com/sameo", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/received_events", "type": "User", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sameo/orgs"}, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/28", "body": "During last week's (03/06) call, we had a discussion as to whether we want to split `sys_utils` into logically separated crates or not.\r\nThe split might cause more issues than advantages, so we may want to start with one single crate, on a single repo, and eventually separate it into finer grain crates (Still from one single repo) if there's an actual reason to do so. However I propose we use a less generic name than `sys_utils`, something like `vmm_sys_utils`.\r\n\r\n@andreeaflorescu @zachreizner wdyt?", "updated_at": "2019-03-11T11:26:54Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/471502213", "author_association": "MEMBER", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-471502213", "created_at": "2019-03-11T11:26:54Z", "id": 471502213, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ3MTUwMjIxMw=="}, {"user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/following{/other_user}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner", "site_admin": false, "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/gists{/gist_id}", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI5MjcxMQ==", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "gravatar_id": "", "id": 292711, "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/events{/privacy}", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/292711?v=4", "login": "zachreizner", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/repos", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/subscriptions", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/followers", "html_url": "https://github.com/zachreizner", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/received_events", "type": "User", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/zachreizner/orgs"}, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/28", "body": "A single crate would be the least risky option in my opinion.\r\nAs far as naming goes, I think `sys_util` (with or without `s`) is fine. The only truly vmm specific parts (`kvm`, `kvm-sys`) are part of a different crate already. On the other hand, prefixing all our crates with `vmm_` does give our crates a certain cohesiveness that could be appealing. For example, it's clear all the `gfx_` crates are from the same group and are designed to work together.", "updated_at": "2019-03-11T17:22:19Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-vmm/community/issues/comments/471637585", "author_association": "MEMBER", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-vmm/community/issues/28#issuecomment-471637585", 